Zein Alabdin Ali is a Syrian vlogger who has been living, working and studying in China since 2010. In that time, Zein's parents and triplet brother and sister have all settled with him in the city of Nanjing. After China optimized its COVID-19 prevention and control policies, this year's Spring Festival saw a resurgence of consumption and a travel boom. Zein and his family shared the scene in Nanjing and sent their Chinese New Year wishes.